WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.395 align:middle line:10%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:03.395 --> 00:00:12.222 align:middle line:90%


00:00:12.222 --> 00:00:14.660 align:middle line:84%
>> Graham Nicholls was one of
those young children who saw

00:00:14.660 --> 00:00:15.680 align:middle line:90%
strangers--

00:00:15.680 --> 00:00:17.660 align:middle line:84%
strangers who were
invisible to others--

00:00:17.660 --> 00:00:20.600 align:middle line:84%
standing at the foot of his bed
as he went to sleep at night.

00:00:20.600 --> 00:00:23.630 align:middle line:84%
Initially frightened by
these experiences, over time

00:00:23.630 --> 00:00:25.880 align:middle line:84%
the opening that occurred
in his psyche began

00:00:25.880 --> 00:00:29.420 align:middle line:84%
showing him future events,
including the London bombings.

00:00:29.420 --> 00:00:32.119 align:middle line:84%
Through his ability to
see beyond time and space,

00:00:32.119 --> 00:00:34.430 align:middle line:84%
Graham learned to see
the interconnectedness

00:00:34.430 --> 00:00:36.290 align:middle line:90%
and love in all things.

00:00:36.290 --> 00:00:39.200 align:middle line:84%
Along with taking part in the
psychic experiments conducted

00:00:39.200 --> 00:00:41.810 align:middle line:84%
by the esteemed biologist
Rupert Sheldrake,

00:00:41.810 --> 00:00:43.700 align:middle line:84%
Graham documented
his experiences

00:00:43.700 --> 00:00:46.190 align:middle line:84%
in his book titled "Avenues
of the Human Spirit."

00:00:46.190 --> 00:00:48.990 align:middle line:90%


00:00:48.990 --> 00:00:50.600 align:middle line:84%
So here we are in
central London.

00:00:50.600 --> 00:00:52.755 align:middle line:90%
It's a busy day, weekday here.

00:00:52.755 --> 00:00:54.380 align:middle line:84%
We have a lot of
construction going on.

00:00:54.380 --> 00:00:55.790 align:middle line:90%
So I'm just saying that.

00:00:55.790 --> 00:00:57.140 align:middle line:90%
If anybody hears some--

00:00:57.140 --> 00:01:00.262 align:middle line:84%
well, I hear a buzz
saw and a hammer--

00:01:00.262 --> 00:01:01.970 align:middle line:84%
just let it blend in
with the background.

00:01:01.970 --> 00:01:05.990 align:middle line:84%
So that said, you've had a
really different kind of life

00:01:05.990 --> 00:01:08.870 align:middle line:84%
from the perspective of
the average person in that

00:01:08.870 --> 00:01:15.800 align:middle line:84%
from a very early age, you were
able to see into other areas

00:01:15.800 --> 00:01:17.570 align:middle line:90%
or other dimensions, realms.

00:01:17.570 --> 00:01:19.880 align:middle line:84%
I'm sure you have your
own way of explaining that

00:01:19.880 --> 00:01:21.680 align:middle line:84%
and maybe you can
give us an idea

00:01:21.680 --> 00:01:25.670 align:middle line:84%
of what started happening
at a very early age for you.

00:01:25.670 --> 00:01:28.880 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, the first experience
that ever happened was when I

00:01:28.880 --> 00:01:31.640 align:middle line:90%
was about five to seven.

00:01:31.640 --> 00:01:33.890 align:middle line:84%
I'm not exactly
sure how old I was.

00:01:33.890 --> 00:01:37.270 align:middle line:84%
But I was living in
an apartment block.

00:01:37.270 --> 00:01:40.610 align:middle line:84%
And I came out of my bedroom
just to go to the toilet

00:01:40.610 --> 00:01:45.560 align:middle line:84%
or whatever as you do during the
night, walked into the hallway,

00:01:45.560 --> 00:01:50.030 align:middle line:84%
and there was a figure
standing in the doorway that

00:01:50.030 --> 00:01:53.927 align:middle line:84%
led out into the landing to
get out of the apartment.

00:01:53.927 --> 00:01:55.760 align:middle line:84%
So there was this figure
just standing there

00:01:55.760 --> 00:01:59.660 align:middle line:90%
staring straight at me.

00:01:59.660 --> 00:02:02.690 align:middle line:84%
And I obviously was
very surprised by this

00:02:02.690 --> 00:02:05.690 align:middle line:90%
and completely overwhelmed.

00:02:05.690 --> 00:02:07.760 align:middle line:90%
I just was terrified really.

00:02:07.760 --> 00:02:11.210 align:middle line:84%
And I dropped to
the ground I think

00:02:11.210 --> 00:02:16.380 align:middle line:84%
to try and get some sense of
something solid from the floor.

00:02:16.380 --> 00:02:19.640 align:middle line:84%
I wanted to feel
like this was real.

00:02:19.640 --> 00:02:25.090 align:middle line:84%
And that was something not what
I would usually experience.

00:02:25.090 --> 00:02:29.510 align:middle line:84%
So I wanted to get this
sense of normality back.

00:02:29.510 --> 00:02:33.410 align:middle line:84%
Then I tried to call
out to my parents.

00:02:33.410 --> 00:02:38.870 align:middle line:84%
And I was so frightened, I
couldn't even make any sound.

00:02:38.870 --> 00:02:43.520 align:middle line:84%
I was just almost frozen
by the experience.

00:02:43.520 --> 00:02:45.590 align:middle line:84%
And then eventually,
it just kind of ended.

00:02:45.590 --> 00:02:48.590 align:middle line:84%
I don't remember the real
details of the whole thing

00:02:48.590 --> 00:02:50.150 align:middle line:90%
because I was so young.

00:02:50.150 --> 00:02:52.660 align:middle line:84%
But that was the thing that
really opened the whole process

00:02:52.660 --> 00:02:53.460 align:middle line:90%
up.

00:02:53.460 --> 00:02:57.410 align:middle line:84%
>> Did you feel different
after this experience?

00:02:57.410 --> 00:02:59.870 align:middle line:84%
>> It seemed to open me
up to a sense that yeah,

00:02:59.870 --> 00:03:02.460 align:middle line:90%
that there was more around.

00:03:02.460 --> 00:03:06.080 align:middle line:84%
And when I was at school
and around other kids,

00:03:06.080 --> 00:03:09.860 align:middle line:84%
I had this sense that
what I understood

00:03:09.860 --> 00:03:14.620 align:middle line:84%
was different to what they were
understanding about the world.

00:03:14.620 --> 00:03:17.510 align:middle line:90%
And religion, for example.

00:03:17.510 --> 00:03:20.120 align:middle line:84%
Some of the children
didn't seem to make sense

00:03:20.120 --> 00:03:23.930 align:middle line:84%
to me because I was starting
to be aware of other things.

00:03:23.930 --> 00:03:26.040 align:middle line:84%
I was getting
impressions as well.

00:03:26.040 --> 00:03:30.350 align:middle line:84%
I have memories of being
in my playground at school

00:03:30.350 --> 00:03:33.080 align:middle line:84%
and just having
impressions of other places

00:03:33.080 --> 00:03:36.675 align:middle line:84%
and even quite cosmic
things like other planets

00:03:36.675 --> 00:03:37.550 align:middle line:90%
and things like that.

00:03:37.550 --> 00:03:41.000 align:middle line:84%
So I was just getting
these impressions coming in

00:03:41.000 --> 00:03:43.400 align:middle line:84%
and then obviously,
that initial experience.

00:03:43.400 --> 00:03:47.600 align:middle line:84%
So the whole thing was giving
me a very different sense

00:03:47.600 --> 00:03:49.970 align:middle line:90%
than the other kids around me.

00:03:49.970 --> 00:03:53.660 align:middle line:84%
>> And in your book, you were
saying that you seemed to have

00:03:53.660 --> 00:03:57.710 align:middle line:84%
a grasp of things very easily
at a very young age that maybe

00:03:57.710 --> 00:03:59.180 align:middle line:90%
other kids didn't as well.

00:03:59.180 --> 00:04:01.460 align:middle line:84%
I mean, even
intellectually, your mind

00:04:01.460 --> 00:04:04.920 align:middle line:84%
was able to expand rather
rapidly at a young age.

00:04:04.920 --> 00:04:05.720 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:04:05.720 --> 00:04:11.330 align:middle line:84%
I was finding the very
structured education system

00:04:11.330 --> 00:04:12.940 align:middle line:90%
much too limiting.

00:04:12.940 --> 00:04:15.500 align:middle line:84%
And I was looking
into other areas

00:04:15.500 --> 00:04:17.459 align:middle line:84%
and was much more
open to things that

00:04:17.459 --> 00:04:22.130 align:middle line:84%
weren't within the bracket
of what I was being told

00:04:22.130 --> 00:04:26.180 align:middle line:84%
and how I was being
told the way things are.

00:04:26.180 --> 00:04:30.830 align:middle line:84%
So it was a real
really different angle

00:04:30.830 --> 00:04:32.000 align:middle line:90%
on the whole wave.

00:04:32.000 --> 00:04:36.320 align:middle line:84%
>> And then to the information
that you had to study as part

00:04:36.320 --> 00:04:39.170 align:middle line:84%
of a matter of course in school,
those things came somewhat

00:04:39.170 --> 00:04:40.160 align:middle line:90%
easily for you?

00:04:40.160 --> 00:04:42.440 align:middle line:84%
Or your brain simply did
not want to go there?

00:04:42.440 --> 00:04:45.080 align:middle line:90%


00:04:45.080 --> 00:04:47.420 align:middle line:84%
>> Certain things did and
certain things didn't.

00:04:47.420 --> 00:04:53.060 align:middle line:84%
I was not convinced by
some of it, like I said,

00:04:53.060 --> 00:04:56.870 align:middle line:84%
and other things I was more
interested in, especially

00:04:56.870 --> 00:05:00.200 align:middle line:84%
history in ancient civilizations
and things like that.

00:05:00.200 --> 00:05:03.030 align:middle line:84%
>> All things mystical were
really appealing to you.

00:05:03.030 --> 00:05:03.830 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:05:03.830 --> 00:05:05.580 align:middle line:84%
Things that seemed to
have some connection

00:05:05.580 --> 00:05:08.510 align:middle line:90%
to what I was experiencing.

00:05:08.510 --> 00:05:10.790 align:middle line:84%
We had one teacher
in particular who

00:05:10.790 --> 00:05:13.910 align:middle line:84%
had traveled to
Mexico, to Egypt,

00:05:13.910 --> 00:05:18.650 align:middle line:84%
and different places that had
a mystical flavor to them.

00:05:18.650 --> 00:05:21.470 align:middle line:84%
And he would give
us lectures on that

00:05:21.470 --> 00:05:24.870 align:middle line:90%
even when we were very small.

00:05:24.870 --> 00:05:28.340 align:middle line:84%
And then I also
had an art teacher.

00:05:28.340 --> 00:05:31.670 align:middle line:84%
She took us to National
Gallery in central London

00:05:31.670 --> 00:05:33.830 align:middle line:84%
and talked about the
mythology behind a lot

00:05:33.830 --> 00:05:36.920 align:middle line:84%
of the great paintings and
great art that you see.

00:05:36.920 --> 00:05:40.850 align:middle line:84%
So there was this sense
of there being more

00:05:40.850 --> 00:05:43.640 align:middle line:90%
to a lot of different levels.

00:05:43.640 --> 00:05:46.470 align:middle line:84%
And I was very drawn to
Greek mythology and all

00:05:46.470 --> 00:05:47.970 align:middle line:84%
these different
mythologies that you

00:05:47.970 --> 00:05:53.505 align:middle line:84%
see within these great
paintings by da Vinci

00:05:53.505 --> 00:05:55.770 align:middle line:90%
and these kinds of artists.

00:05:55.770 --> 00:05:58.120 align:middle line:84%
So I think that was something
that really drew me.

00:05:58.120 --> 00:05:58.920 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:05:58.920 --> 00:06:00.690 align:middle line:84%
And when normally at age
six, seven, and eight,

00:06:00.690 --> 00:06:02.023 align:middle line:90%
that wouldn't be the first draw.

00:06:02.023 --> 00:06:03.255 align:middle line:90%
But there you were.

00:06:03.255 --> 00:06:05.310 align:middle line:84%
By 12 years old,
you were actually

00:06:05.310 --> 00:06:09.788 align:middle line:84%
starting to have experiences,
out of body experiences.

00:06:09.788 --> 00:06:12.080 align:middle line:84%
Can you talk a little bit
about that and what happened?

00:06:12.080 --> 00:06:14.190 align:middle line:84%
And as we go further
along in this,

00:06:14.190 --> 00:06:17.300 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to pick your brain as
to some of the things you saw.

00:06:17.300 --> 00:06:19.050 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:06:19.050 --> 00:06:24.190 align:middle line:84%
Well, the very first out of body
experiences were very short.

00:06:24.190 --> 00:06:25.650 align:middle line:90%
They weren't the classic--

00:06:25.650 --> 00:06:28.830 align:middle line:84%
a lot of people describe this
idea of coming out of the body

00:06:28.830 --> 00:06:31.830 align:middle line:84%
and then looking down
at yourself from above.

00:06:31.830 --> 00:06:36.450 align:middle line:84%
My very first experience
is I was upright

00:06:36.450 --> 00:06:38.640 align:middle line:84%
as if I was standing in
the middle of the room,

00:06:38.640 --> 00:06:42.810 align:middle line:84%
but I was floating a few
feet above the ground.

00:06:42.810 --> 00:06:46.320 align:middle line:84%
So very different to
what a lot of people

00:06:46.320 --> 00:06:50.590 align:middle line:84%
will just describe when they
have out of body experiences.

00:06:50.590 --> 00:06:52.680 align:middle line:90%
And they were always in the way.

00:06:52.680 --> 00:06:54.150 align:middle line:90%
I was always upright.

00:06:54.150 --> 00:06:57.810 align:middle line:84%
And I had maybe two or
three of those initially.

00:06:57.810 --> 00:07:00.310 align:middle line:90%
Only lasted a few seconds.

00:07:00.310 --> 00:07:05.310 align:middle line:84%
And then I saw
something on the TV

00:07:05.310 --> 00:07:09.990 align:middle line:84%
or read something about
how astral projection

00:07:09.990 --> 00:07:13.000 align:middle line:84%
or out of body experiences
can be induced.

00:07:13.000 --> 00:07:16.440 align:middle line:84%
And these things can
lead you somewhere.

00:07:16.440 --> 00:07:18.990 align:middle line:84%
You can travel around
the world or you

00:07:18.990 --> 00:07:21.280 align:middle line:84%
can explore your spirituality
through them and things

00:07:21.280 --> 00:07:22.080 align:middle line:90%
like that.

00:07:22.080 --> 00:07:26.760 align:middle line:84%
So I then went looking
for a book on the subject.

00:07:26.760 --> 00:07:28.260 align:middle line:84%
And actually not
very far from here,

00:07:28.260 --> 00:07:32.880 align:middle line:84%
I found a book shop that had
one book by a parapsychologist

00:07:32.880 --> 00:07:35.640 align:middle line:84%
called Janet Lee
Mitchell, which was quite

00:07:35.640 --> 00:07:37.950 align:middle line:90%
scientific in its outlook.

00:07:37.950 --> 00:07:44.680 align:middle line:84%
But it had this sense that this
was a real objective thing.

00:07:44.680 --> 00:07:47.640 align:middle line:84%
A lot of the books out
there are much more

00:07:47.640 --> 00:07:52.410 align:middle line:84%
dreamy or kind of
beyond the normal pale

00:07:52.410 --> 00:07:53.650 align:middle line:90%
of what we understand.

00:07:53.650 --> 00:07:55.690 align:middle line:90%
But this book was quite solid.

00:07:55.690 --> 00:07:59.762 align:middle line:84%
So that was a good place
for me to start, in a way.

00:07:59.762 --> 00:08:00.720 align:middle line:90%
So I read through that.

00:08:00.720 --> 00:08:02.390 align:middle line:84%
And then towards the
back of the book,

00:08:02.390 --> 00:08:05.340 align:middle line:84%
there was some really
basic techniques

00:08:05.340 --> 00:08:09.730 align:middle line:84%
that were probably way
too simple in a way.

00:08:09.730 --> 00:08:13.030 align:middle line:84%
But I persevered with it, and
I went through these techniques

00:08:13.030 --> 00:08:13.830 align:middle line:90%
for about--

00:08:13.830 --> 00:08:15.510 align:middle line:90%
it took me about six months.

00:08:15.510 --> 00:08:17.080 align:middle line:84%
>> Yeah, you were
really dedicated.

00:08:17.080 --> 00:08:17.360 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:08:17.360 --> 00:08:19.560 align:middle line:84%
>> You'd lie there when most
kids are daydreaming and trying

00:08:19.560 --> 00:08:21.643 align:middle line:84%
to go to sleep, and you
are trying to catapult out

00:08:21.643 --> 00:08:24.183 align:middle line:84%
of your body at
such a young age.

00:08:24.183 --> 00:08:25.350 align:middle line:90%
>> And I did it every night.

00:08:25.350 --> 00:08:25.920 align:middle line:90%
>> Every night.

00:08:25.920 --> 00:08:26.770 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:08:26.770 --> 00:08:29.910 align:middle line:84%
I was impressed with
your persistence.

00:08:29.910 --> 00:08:30.750 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:08:30.750 --> 00:08:35.850 align:middle line:90%
And then I think I was about 14.

00:08:35.850 --> 00:08:38.909 align:middle line:84%
And I had my first induced
out of body experience,

00:08:38.909 --> 00:08:41.190 align:middle line:84%
which was just like
this surge of energy,

00:08:41.190 --> 00:08:44.500 align:middle line:84%
almost like an electric
bolt went through my body,

00:08:44.500 --> 00:08:48.330 align:middle line:84%
just shot out my
body above myself

00:08:48.330 --> 00:08:54.600 align:middle line:84%
around 16, something like
that, looking down at myself.

00:08:54.600 --> 00:08:58.350 align:middle line:84%
And there was a
kind of bluish glow

00:08:58.350 --> 00:09:01.600 align:middle line:84%
coming off of the
second body I was in.

00:09:01.600 --> 00:09:05.250 align:middle line:84%
And the whole room seemed
to be lit from that,

00:09:05.250 --> 00:09:07.360 align:middle line:90%
so I could look around the room.

00:09:07.360 --> 00:09:09.555 align:middle line:84%
But I couldn't move other
than kind of rotating.

00:09:09.555 --> 00:09:12.250 align:middle line:90%


00:09:12.250 --> 00:09:15.640 align:middle line:84%
And looking at myself
laying on the bed,

00:09:15.640 --> 00:09:17.350 align:middle line:90%
it didn't feel like me.

00:09:17.350 --> 00:09:21.900 align:middle line:84%
It just felt almost
like a sculpture.

00:09:21.900 --> 00:09:24.660 align:middle line:84%
>> Like Madam Tussaud's
Museum of Wax Art.

00:09:24.660 --> 00:09:25.860 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:09:25.860 --> 00:09:27.990 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I almost had
to check that it was me

00:09:27.990 --> 00:09:29.490 align:middle line:84%
because I didn't
really feel like I

00:09:29.490 --> 00:09:33.310 align:middle line:84%
had much of a relationship
with the body laying there.

00:09:33.310 --> 00:09:35.880 align:middle line:84%
I just knew logically
that it must be me

00:09:35.880 --> 00:09:38.795 align:middle line:90%
because this is my room.

00:09:38.795 --> 00:09:40.510 align:middle line:84%
>> That looks like
me lying there.

00:09:40.510 --> 00:09:41.310 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:09:41.310 --> 00:09:46.230 align:middle line:84%
But you were actually the source
of the illumination in the room

00:09:46.230 --> 00:09:47.460 align:middle line:90%
and the observer in the room.

00:09:47.460 --> 00:09:50.400 align:middle line:84%
And this is the holy grail
in all spiritual journeys

00:09:50.400 --> 00:09:55.520 align:middle line:84%
that people are trying to get
to know that part of themselves

00:09:55.520 --> 00:09:57.720 align:middle line:84%
or to understand that
part of themselves better.

00:09:57.720 --> 00:09:58.520 align:middle line:90%
>> Sure.

00:09:58.520 --> 00:10:01.200 align:middle line:84%
>> And you were having some
very direct experiences.

00:10:01.200 --> 00:10:03.870 align:middle line:84%
>> I think that's the
key, this directness,

00:10:03.870 --> 00:10:07.040 align:middle line:84%
this sense of-- that's what's
really amazing about out

00:10:07.040 --> 00:10:11.100 align:middle line:84%
of body experiences is that they
can give us this direct link

00:10:11.100 --> 00:10:14.760 align:middle line:84%
or direct experience of
something more than ourselves.

00:10:14.760 --> 00:10:17.460 align:middle line:84%
I can't really think
of any other practice

00:10:17.460 --> 00:10:20.050 align:middle line:84%
that you can do that can
give you that as much.

00:10:20.050 --> 00:10:20.850 align:middle line:90%
>> Very true.

00:10:20.850 --> 00:10:23.490 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes people
do have this experience

00:10:23.490 --> 00:10:27.150 align:middle line:84%
without even knowing what it
is, a feeling of disorientation.

00:10:27.150 --> 00:10:31.260 align:middle line:84%
I've had a few little accidental
out of body experiences.

00:10:31.260 --> 00:10:36.360 align:middle line:84%
In fact, one in which I ended up
flying down a flight of stairs

00:10:36.360 --> 00:10:39.540 align:middle line:84%
and landed because I thought I
was concerned about something

00:10:39.540 --> 00:10:41.850 align:middle line:84%
happening downstairs
with my son,

00:10:41.850 --> 00:10:44.520 align:middle line:84%
landed upside down in
the middle of the room,

00:10:44.520 --> 00:10:46.680 align:middle line:84%
and he was out of
his body sitting up

00:10:46.680 --> 00:10:48.725 align:middle line:90%
watching me out of my body.

00:10:48.725 --> 00:10:50.130 align:middle line:90%
And it was all so--

00:10:50.130 --> 00:10:51.900 align:middle line:84%
I was so embarrassed
of being upside down,

00:10:51.900 --> 00:10:55.140 align:middle line:84%
I actually snapped myself
back into my physical body.

00:10:55.140 --> 00:10:56.180 align:middle line:90%
I thought this is bad.

00:10:56.180 --> 00:10:59.317 align:middle line:84%
I'm hanging here like
a bat upside down

00:10:59.317 --> 00:11:00.400 align:middle line:90%
in the middle of the room.

00:11:00.400 --> 00:11:03.450 align:middle line:84%
[LAUGHS] And just because
I'd simply flown down

00:11:03.450 --> 00:11:06.290 align:middle line:84%
the stairs headfirst and just
landed that way more or less.

00:11:06.290 --> 00:11:10.290 align:middle line:84%
And that wasn't a particularly
spiritual opening for me.

00:11:10.290 --> 00:11:13.390 align:middle line:84%
It was just a source of
embarrassment in that moment.

00:11:13.390 --> 00:11:17.220 align:middle line:84%
And we have silly little
things like this that happen

00:11:17.220 --> 00:11:20.280 align:middle line:84%
or just a sense of
something being disorienting

00:11:20.280 --> 00:11:23.710 align:middle line:84%
in a place of
patterns and color.

00:11:23.710 --> 00:11:25.650 align:middle line:84%
And that is actually
that crossover place

00:11:25.650 --> 00:11:27.610 align:middle line:90%
for a lot of people, isn't it?

00:11:27.610 --> 00:11:28.410 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:11:28.410 --> 00:11:32.320 align:middle line:84%
I think there's a kind
of spectrum experiences.

00:11:32.320 --> 00:11:35.190 align:middle line:84%
And I think you've
got the more--

00:11:35.190 --> 00:11:38.400 align:middle line:84%
just a kind of gut
feeling that you get.

00:11:38.400 --> 00:11:41.970 align:middle line:84%
That's like the beginning place
maybe, a sense of something

00:11:41.970 --> 00:11:45.210 align:middle line:84%
else or that awareness
that almost everyone has,

00:11:45.210 --> 00:11:48.090 align:middle line:84%
or a sense that
someone they know

00:11:48.090 --> 00:11:51.180 align:middle line:84%
is going to phone them
shortly, and then they do.

00:11:51.180 --> 00:11:55.150 align:middle line:84%
Those kind of gut experiences
at the beginning part.

00:11:55.150 --> 00:11:57.930 align:middle line:84%
But then I think you
go along that spectrum

00:11:57.930 --> 00:12:01.530 align:middle line:84%
and you get to something
like remote viewing

00:12:01.530 --> 00:12:03.660 align:middle line:84%
or this idea of trying
to perceive something

00:12:03.660 --> 00:12:04.470 align:middle line:90%
at a distance.

00:12:04.470 --> 00:12:09.600 align:middle line:84%
And then you get to a more
full separation experience,

00:12:09.600 --> 00:12:12.190 align:middle line:84%
which is what the out
of body experience is,

00:12:12.190 --> 00:12:13.600 align:middle line:90%
in my understanding.

00:12:13.600 --> 00:12:16.170 align:middle line:84%
>> And so you learned how to
control it then by the age

00:12:16.170 --> 00:12:17.310 align:middle line:90%
of about 14.

00:12:17.310 --> 00:12:19.260 align:middle line:90%
And were you able--

00:12:19.260 --> 00:12:21.913 align:middle line:84%
I mean, off and on-- not
necessarily every day

00:12:21.913 --> 00:12:23.580 align:middle line:84%
at every moment you
chose-- but were you

00:12:23.580 --> 00:12:27.000 align:middle line:84%
able to continually project
yourself out of body

00:12:27.000 --> 00:12:28.870 align:middle line:90%
after that into this time?

00:12:28.870 --> 00:12:31.680 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, once I had the
very first experience,

00:12:31.680 --> 00:12:34.320 align:middle line:84%
it was almost like I'd
open the floodgates.

00:12:34.320 --> 00:12:38.010 align:middle line:84%
And then I was having a lot
more out of body experiences.

00:12:38.010 --> 00:12:41.790 align:middle line:84%
But it took me a long time
to get comfortable with going

00:12:41.790 --> 00:12:43.170 align:middle line:90%
further from myself.

00:12:43.170 --> 00:12:46.050 align:middle line:90%


00:12:46.050 --> 00:12:50.650 align:middle line:84%
The bedroom was almost like
my limit for a long time.

00:12:50.650 --> 00:12:52.945 align:middle line:84%
And I think that was to do
with my own psychological

00:12:52.945 --> 00:12:53.745 align:middle line:90%
limitations.

00:12:53.745 --> 00:12:54.420 align:middle line:90%
>> Fear.

00:12:54.420 --> 00:12:55.160 align:middle line:90%
>> Fear, sure.

00:12:55.160 --> 00:12:55.960 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:12:55.960 --> 00:13:00.120 align:middle line:84%
That going outside of my
house or going further afield

00:13:00.120 --> 00:13:01.830 align:middle line:90%
might lead to me--

00:13:01.830 --> 00:13:03.740 align:middle line:84%
I don't know-- dying
or something like that.

00:13:03.740 --> 00:13:04.110 align:middle line:90%
>> Sure.

00:13:04.110 --> 00:13:05.100 align:middle line:90%
Understandable.

00:13:05.100 --> 00:13:07.720 align:middle line:84%
>> So it took me a long
time to get over that.

00:13:07.720 --> 00:13:10.710 align:middle line:84%
But then eventually,
I pushed through--

00:13:10.710 --> 00:13:13.080 align:middle line:84%
literally pushed
through the window

00:13:13.080 --> 00:13:16.290 align:middle line:84%
and moved out into
the street and then

00:13:16.290 --> 00:13:20.230 align:middle line:84%
started to move around the local
area that I was familiar with.

00:13:20.230 --> 00:13:23.100 align:middle line:84%
And over time, gradually moved
further and further afield.

00:13:23.100 --> 00:13:26.010 align:middle line:90%
So that was the process.

00:13:26.010 --> 00:13:28.110 align:middle line:84%
>> And as I was reading
this in your book,

00:13:28.110 --> 00:13:33.870 align:middle line:84%
you would talk about the
luminescence of objects,

00:13:33.870 --> 00:13:36.233 align:middle line:90%
of trees, and inanimate objects.

00:13:36.233 --> 00:13:37.650 align:middle line:84%
I remember you
saying at one point

00:13:37.650 --> 00:13:40.560 align:middle line:84%
that sometimes
inanimate objects almost

00:13:40.560 --> 00:13:44.070 align:middle line:84%
seemed to possess more life
force than animate objects.

00:13:44.070 --> 00:13:46.650 align:middle line:84%
And you spoke of trees
on a number of occasions

00:13:46.650 --> 00:13:48.990 align:middle line:84%
because you would
go out into nature

00:13:48.990 --> 00:13:50.220 align:middle line:90%
and do quite a bit of this.

00:13:50.220 --> 00:13:53.640 align:middle line:84%
And can you talk about that
a little bit, some of what

00:13:53.640 --> 00:13:56.550 align:middle line:84%
you saw to bring to
those who have not

00:13:56.550 --> 00:14:01.290 align:middle line:84%
had this experience the
nature energetically of a tree

00:14:01.290 --> 00:14:05.160 align:middle line:90%
or a building or whatnot?

00:14:05.160 --> 00:14:07.890 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I think it's
maybe something to do with

00:14:07.890 --> 00:14:12.000 align:middle line:84%
the frequency that
particular things operate on.

00:14:12.000 --> 00:14:14.970 align:middle line:84%
When you're in a building
like this that's been here

00:14:14.970 --> 00:14:17.640 align:middle line:84%
for a long time
and has always had

00:14:17.640 --> 00:14:20.480 align:middle line:84%
this sense of spiritual
activity going on,

00:14:20.480 --> 00:14:24.860 align:middle line:84%
I think that it builds up
this aura, if you like,

00:14:24.860 --> 00:14:27.050 align:middle line:84%
or some kind of
impression that goes

00:14:27.050 --> 00:14:30.980 align:middle line:84%
into the very fabric
of the building.

00:14:30.980 --> 00:14:34.640 align:middle line:84%
And I think when I was
having my first experiences,

00:14:34.640 --> 00:14:36.510 align:middle line:90%
I was picking up on that.

00:14:36.510 --> 00:14:39.620 align:middle line:84%
So I would go past a
building that's very old.

00:14:39.620 --> 00:14:44.300 align:middle line:84%
I mean, some buildings in
London can be 1,000 years old.

00:14:44.300 --> 00:14:47.240 align:middle line:84%
So as you pass that
building, I would

00:14:47.240 --> 00:14:51.930 align:middle line:84%
see this sense of the energy
nature of the building.

00:14:51.930 --> 00:14:54.100 align:middle line:84%
Maybe its true
form, if you like,

00:14:54.100 --> 00:14:58.010 align:middle line:84%
or maybe just some
underlying level of it.

00:14:58.010 --> 00:15:00.590 align:middle line:84%
>> And what would
that look like?

00:15:00.590 --> 00:15:05.630 align:middle line:84%
>> Often, it would look
almost like heat signatures,

00:15:05.630 --> 00:15:09.200 align:middle line:84%
almost like different
colors radiating out.

00:15:09.200 --> 00:15:12.980 align:middle line:84%
I often found that there
were oranges and yellows.

00:15:12.980 --> 00:15:14.910 align:middle line:84%
But it would depend
on the building,

00:15:14.910 --> 00:15:17.760 align:middle line:84%
and it would maybe depend
on what the connection was

00:15:17.760 --> 00:15:18.560 align:middle line:90%
with the building.

00:15:18.560 --> 00:15:21.830 align:middle line:84%
So that was something that
was interesting to explore

00:15:21.830 --> 00:15:25.340 align:middle line:84%
to really look at what that
signature was and see if that

00:15:25.340 --> 00:15:28.640 align:middle line:84%
had any relationship
to what that

00:15:28.640 --> 00:15:32.750 align:middle line:84%
might mean, what that building
was used for, things like that.

00:15:32.750 --> 00:15:34.400 align:middle line:84%
But then on other
occasions, like I

00:15:34.400 --> 00:15:39.380 align:middle line:84%
was saying, with trees
or with human beings,

00:15:39.380 --> 00:15:43.130 align:middle line:84%
you might be more on that
frequency on another occasion.

00:15:43.130 --> 00:15:46.730 align:middle line:84%
And I would see almost
like the life force

00:15:46.730 --> 00:15:49.520 align:middle line:84%
moving through the
trunk of the tree

00:15:49.520 --> 00:15:52.190 align:middle line:84%
or moving through
the leaves and get

00:15:52.190 --> 00:15:55.280 align:middle line:84%
this sense of the whole
process of the plant

00:15:55.280 --> 00:15:59.750 align:middle line:84%
drawing up nutrients from the
soil and the whole spectrum

00:15:59.750 --> 00:16:00.830 align:middle line:90%
of life.

00:16:00.830 --> 00:16:03.060 align:middle line:84%
But you would see on
a different level.

00:16:03.060 --> 00:16:05.660 align:middle line:84%
And through this
outer body perception,

00:16:05.660 --> 00:16:07.430 align:middle line:84%
it was like you could
go right into it

00:16:07.430 --> 00:16:11.960 align:middle line:84%
and explore the whole
nature of that plant.

00:16:11.960 --> 00:16:15.200 align:middle line:84%
Because although maybe we would
assume that we're using eyes,

00:16:15.200 --> 00:16:19.520 align:middle line:84%
and sometimes we would sense
a body and things like that,

00:16:19.520 --> 00:16:22.730 align:middle line:84%
I came to the conclusion
that that's just something

00:16:22.730 --> 00:16:23.720 align:middle line:90%
that we assume.

00:16:23.720 --> 00:16:26.030 align:middle line:84%
But really, we're
not using eyes.

00:16:26.030 --> 00:16:29.750 align:middle line:84%
It's almost like a direct
link with our consciousness.

00:16:29.750 --> 00:16:34.430 align:middle line:84%
So we can, in my experience,
directly link with a plant

00:16:34.430 --> 00:16:37.040 align:middle line:84%
or directly link
with another person

00:16:37.040 --> 00:16:40.940 align:middle line:84%
and maybe get some impression
from that and draw from that.

00:16:40.940 --> 00:16:44.240 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it opens up the whole
idea of psychical abilities

00:16:44.240 --> 00:16:46.820 align:middle line:90%
and those kinds of ideas really.

00:16:46.820 --> 00:16:49.100 align:middle line:90%
>> And you also had--

00:16:49.100 --> 00:16:51.200 align:middle line:84%
I remember one experience
I was reading about

00:16:51.200 --> 00:16:55.870 align:middle line:84%
in which you were emerging with
a little animal in the forest.

00:16:55.870 --> 00:16:56.910 align:middle line:90%
It was so sweet.

00:16:56.910 --> 00:16:57.950 align:middle line:90%
Can you talk about that?

00:16:57.950 --> 00:17:02.000 align:middle line:84%
I just loved that
part of the story.

00:17:02.000 --> 00:17:06.970 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I used to go to
this open nature area to do--

00:17:06.970 --> 00:17:09.720 align:middle line:84%
>> Was this the new forest
area or a different area?

00:17:09.720 --> 00:17:12.079 align:middle line:84%
>> This was actually just
in London that experience

00:17:12.079 --> 00:17:17.390 align:middle line:84%
happened, on Hampstead Heath,
which is a big open heath area.

00:17:17.390 --> 00:17:19.760 align:middle line:84%
And I used to go there
a lot just to meditate

00:17:19.760 --> 00:17:21.740 align:middle line:90%
and to do different practices.

00:17:21.740 --> 00:17:24.770 align:middle line:84%
And on this particular
day, I was looking out

00:17:24.770 --> 00:17:29.820 align:middle line:84%
into the darkness of the trees
and everything around me.

00:17:29.820 --> 00:17:32.030 align:middle line:84%
And I started to see
these points of light

00:17:32.030 --> 00:17:36.710 align:middle line:84%
appearing as I was going
deeper into my state of trance,

00:17:36.710 --> 00:17:39.980 align:middle line:84%
if you like, or whatever
you want to call it.

00:17:39.980 --> 00:17:43.970 align:middle line:84%
And I started to see these
points of light all around me.

00:17:43.970 --> 00:17:47.510 align:middle line:84%
And then I realized as I
focused on them more and more

00:17:47.510 --> 00:17:51.070 align:middle line:84%
that these points of
light were little animals.

00:17:51.070 --> 00:17:52.890 align:middle line:90%
They were like consciousness.

00:17:52.890 --> 00:17:59.330 align:middle line:84%
Little vole or
mouse-like creatures.

00:17:59.330 --> 00:18:01.370 align:middle line:84%
And as I focus more
and more, I seem

00:18:01.370 --> 00:18:03.590 align:middle line:84%
to go deeper and deeper
into this connection

00:18:03.590 --> 00:18:05.960 align:middle line:90%
with these other creatures.

00:18:05.960 --> 00:18:09.680 align:middle line:84%
And eventually, it was
like I tuned into the life

00:18:09.680 --> 00:18:14.510 align:middle line:90%
cycle of one of these voles.

00:18:14.510 --> 00:18:16.610 align:middle line:84%
And I experienced
the whole process

00:18:16.610 --> 00:18:20.960 align:middle line:84%
of it going into its home, being
around the other creatures,

00:18:20.960 --> 00:18:25.220 align:middle line:84%
coming out, looking for
food and foraging around,

00:18:25.220 --> 00:18:27.920 align:middle line:84%
this whole experience
of its life.

00:18:27.920 --> 00:18:33.920 align:middle line:84%
And then eventually, one day,
I went out in the daylight.

00:18:33.920 --> 00:18:37.190 align:middle line:90%
And a bird of prey basically--

00:18:37.190 --> 00:18:41.030 align:middle line:84%
I remember the feeling, the
talons basically coming around

00:18:41.030 --> 00:18:42.840 align:middle line:90%
me in this experience.

00:18:42.840 --> 00:18:44.730 align:middle line:90%
And then the experience ending.

00:18:44.730 --> 00:18:46.520 align:middle line:90%
>> Just lights went out.

00:18:46.520 --> 00:18:49.520 align:middle line:84%
And when you were
talking about this,

00:18:49.520 --> 00:18:53.960 align:middle line:84%
you mentioned that there
was this sense of fear

00:18:53.960 --> 00:18:57.200 align:middle line:84%
in this animal just to go
out and get what it needed

00:18:57.200 --> 00:18:59.030 align:middle line:90%
to get and bring it back.

00:18:59.030 --> 00:19:02.270 align:middle line:90%
I mean, just the basic survival.

00:19:02.270 --> 00:19:05.870 align:middle line:84%
There was always a sense
of fear in the little body,

00:19:05.870 --> 00:19:07.930 align:middle line:84%
just getting
through another day.

00:19:07.930 --> 00:19:10.130 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah, a sense of--

00:19:10.130 --> 00:19:11.600 align:middle line:90%
especially at daylight.

00:19:11.600 --> 00:19:17.080 align:middle line:84%
The daylight was quite
fearful and dangerous.

00:19:17.080 --> 00:19:22.420 align:middle line:84%
And also a sense of awareness
of all the other creatures.

00:19:22.420 --> 00:19:26.800 align:middle line:84%
It was almost like they were
very joined much more than I

00:19:26.800 --> 00:19:28.797 align:middle line:90%
experience in a human sense.

00:19:28.797 --> 00:19:31.130 align:middle line:84%
>> They had to be aware of
where the other species were,

00:19:31.130 --> 00:19:33.190 align:middle line:84%
what they were doing,
whether they were in danger,

00:19:33.190 --> 00:19:34.150 align:middle line:90%
whether they were safe.

00:19:34.150 --> 00:19:35.370 align:middle line:90%
>> And each other as well.

00:19:35.370 --> 00:19:36.850 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:19:36.850 --> 00:19:40.110 align:middle line:84%
it's almost like their survival
instinct was joining together.

00:19:40.110 --> 00:19:41.680 align:middle line:90%
And that's how they operated.

00:19:41.680 --> 00:19:45.020 align:middle line:84%
So yeah, that was a very
interesting experience.

00:19:45.020 --> 00:19:49.270 align:middle line:84%
It was like this opened up this
real insight to other animals

00:19:49.270 --> 00:19:52.150 align:middle line:84%
and that we're all on
a continuum of life.

00:19:52.150 --> 00:19:55.480 align:middle line:84%
It's not we're human and
they're something else.

00:19:55.480 --> 00:19:58.990 align:middle line:84%
We're all part of the process
of life is how I see it.

00:19:58.990 --> 00:20:02.160 align:middle line:84%
>> And this really is the theme
throughout the book is once

00:20:02.160 --> 00:20:05.890 align:middle line:84%
you've started being able to
navigate in these other areas

00:20:05.890 --> 00:20:10.210 align:middle line:84%
of consciousness, this sense of
connectivity where human beings

00:20:10.210 --> 00:20:13.310 align:middle line:90%
feel distinctly separate.

00:20:13.310 --> 00:20:16.900 align:middle line:84%
>> Yeah, I think definitely the
theme running through is that

00:20:16.900 --> 00:20:19.930 align:middle line:84%
from this direct experience,
there is this sense

00:20:19.930 --> 00:20:24.100 align:middle line:84%
of interconnectedness or of
oneness or that we're not all

00:20:24.100 --> 00:20:29.570 align:middle line:84%
divided up, which I think is
quite an age old spiritual

00:20:29.570 --> 00:20:30.370 align:middle line:90%
teaching.

00:20:30.370 --> 00:20:32.710 align:middle line:84%
But I think through
experiences like this,

00:20:32.710 --> 00:20:36.430 align:middle line:84%
we can directly
encounter that, and we

00:20:36.430 --> 00:20:40.980 align:middle line:84%
can know that rather than
just kind of theorize about it

00:20:40.980 --> 00:20:42.090 align:middle line:90%
or whatever.

00:20:42.090 --> 00:20:45.070 align:middle line:84%
So that's what I think
is really valuable that I

00:20:45.070 --> 00:20:46.740 align:middle line:90%
was trying to get across.

00:20:46.740 --> 00:20:50.440 align:middle line:84%
And that it doesn't really
matter the context either.

00:20:50.440 --> 00:20:53.170 align:middle line:84%
I mean, talking about
the fact that I grew up

00:20:53.170 --> 00:20:57.130 align:middle line:84%
in quite a rough part of
London and things like that,

00:20:57.130 --> 00:20:59.080 align:middle line:84%
I think that all
added to the process

00:20:59.080 --> 00:21:03.940 align:middle line:84%
because it gave me this
sense of separation

00:21:03.940 --> 00:21:06.970 align:middle line:84%
maybe to a lot of
the traditional ideas

00:21:06.970 --> 00:21:10.363 align:middle line:84%
of spirituality, but not in a
way that I thought they were

00:21:10.363 --> 00:21:11.530 align:middle line:90%
wrong or anything like that.

00:21:11.530 --> 00:21:15.460 align:middle line:84%
But a separation that I needed
something slightly different

00:21:15.460 --> 00:21:18.850 align:middle line:84%
to speak to me
because I was coming

00:21:18.850 --> 00:21:22.180 align:middle line:84%
from a slightly different
social cultural experience

00:21:22.180 --> 00:21:25.690 align:middle line:84%
to what most people who
talk about these things are.

00:21:25.690 --> 00:21:28.600 align:middle line:84%
So I think that was important
with writing the book as well.

00:21:28.600 --> 00:21:28.880 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:21:28.880 --> 00:21:30.963 align:middle line:84%
And you had to deal with
your own survival issues,

00:21:30.963 --> 00:21:33.280 align:middle line:84%
being mugged and the like,
and who you were going

00:21:33.280 --> 00:21:36.160 align:middle line:90%
to create an alliance with.

00:21:36.160 --> 00:21:40.948 align:middle line:90%
And you have these experiences--

